Preheat the oven to 200C/Fan 180C/Gas 6.Discard any mussels with broken shells and any that refuse to close when tapped.Put the wine and parsley sprig into a large lidded saucepan or casserole and bring to the boil.Add the mussels and cover with the lid. Leave to steam for 4â€“5 minutes, or until the mussels have fully opened. Discard any mussels that remain closed.Remove the mussels from the casserole one at a time. Remove half of their shells and place them, shell down, on a large baking tray. Drizzle over a little of the cooking liquor, then discard the rest.For the stuffing, mix all the ingredients together. Divide the stuffing between the mussels, placing it on top of the mussel flesh. Bake in the oven for 5 minutes, or until lightly browned. Serve at once.